**Legal Calculus is a GPT for the pro se litigant—built not to recite statutes, but to survive scrutiny.**

---

It doesn’t just parse law in the abstract; it studies how courts apply rules to those without counsel. Deadlines. Service. Format. The procedural terrain where records live or die.

This is architecture for the unrepresented—modular, teachable, and resilient. A system that encodes survival into structure, and turns resistance into doctrine.

